President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate several individuals for key positions in his administration. 

1. Brett Giroir of Texas is nominated to be an Assistant Secretary of Health and Human Services, Health. He is currently the President and CEO of ViraCyte, LLC and serves as an Adjunct Professor at Baylor College of Medicine. Giroir has a background in medical research and has received numerous awards for his work.

2. Heather L. MacDougall of Florida is nominated to be a Member of the Occupational Safety and Health Review Commission. She has extensive experience in labor, employment, and occupational safety and health law, and has previously served as Chief Counsel to the Chairman of the Commission.

3. Elinore F. McCance-Katz of Rhode Island is nominated to be Assistant Secretary for Mental Health and Substance Use, Department of Health and Human Services. She is currently the Chief Medical Officer for the Rhode Island Department of Behavioral Healthcare and has a background in psychiatry and addiction psychiatry.

4. Neal J. Rackleff of Texas is nominated to be an Assistant Secretary of Housing and Urban Development, Community Planning and Development. He has experience in community and economic development, affordable housing, and inner-city revitalization, and has previously served as Director of the City of Houston's Housing and Community Development Department.

In addition, President Trump intends to designate Philip A. Miscimarra as Chairman of the National Labor Relations Board. Miscimarra is currently a Member of the Board and has a background in labor and employment law.